defaultThe AR5 Physical Science Basis 
defaultSummary for Policy Makers (
defaultSPM
default)
default was approved by the Session of Working Group 1; IPCC proce
defaultdures require that such Sessions are open to all governments.  The “Principles Governing IPCC Work” state that “
defaultIPCC reports should be neutral with respect to policy
default” and the Session was conducted with this principle in mind. Indeed, from the Chair, Co-Cha
defaultir Prof Thomas Stocker stated that scientific integrity should be paramount in the Session’s deliberations.  
defaultThe approval process might best be described as a dialogue between the Government representatives and the Lead Authors to ensure conclusions were 
defaultwell founded, balanced, relevant and communicated clearly. The last word on the content was always provided by the Lead Authors present. 
default&#xa0;defaultThe UK has committed to reducing its greenhouse gas emissions by 80% on 1990 levels by 2050. This level was set following the advice of the independent Committee on Climate Change (CCC). This represents the CCC’s view of 
defaultan appropriate UK share of a global emissions reduction pathway that limits c
defaultentral estimates of global temperature increase by 2100 to 2°C over pre-industrial levels, and 
defaultkeeps 
defaultthe likelihood of a 4°C increase very low
default 
default(e.g. less than 1%).
