defaultn Climate Change, having considered the evidence in the Fifth Assessment Report, recently concluded that t
defaulthe climate objective
default 
defaultand the global emissions reduction required to achieve it remain an appropriate basis for 
defaultthe UK’s 
defaultpolicy, both because of the ve
defaultry significant risks associated with dangerous climate change and the costs of delayed-action pathways.
